column5: Just wanted to say hello to everyone here now that I am living in Ontario. Manitoba is such a great fishery although Ontario does have its Muskie and Largemouth as well as salmonoids and trout. Whoo Hoo Ontario is great!  Looking forward to posting on the site regularly.  If anyone has questions about Manitoba please feel free to ask.
Welcome to the board!Where in Ontario do you live.
I'm in Markham although I have fished all over Ontario... You?
Sweet... Close to all the big eyes.... Never fished the Bay yet
I'm gonna take the kids and wife out today for awhile not expecting much but some good family time.
Welcome aboad Manitoba.  You picked a great province to fish in.  I usually spend 3 weeks a year up there ... four this year.  Hope you all got cheaper gas up there !    (HA HA HA).
Welcome to the Board Rob, You'll be addicted in no time  .  Just so you know...we like pictures  Maureen
Welcome Rob.  I used to live in Flin Flon, Manitoba.  Alot of rock that's for sure.  Do they still have Orbit?  You'll love it here, Ontario and this board  Joey
Just so everyone is aware... I'm from Manitoba and currently live in Markham Ontario..... Moved here 7 years ago
Must be the name that's confusing everyone  Joey
....Nice to have you on board Rob.
Welcome aboard, you have some impressive fish in your gallery.  Mike
